==English==
===Pronunciation===
*dī'mənd, /ˈdaɪmənd/, /"daIm@nd/


===Adjective===
'''diamond''' 

#Consisting of a glimmering shining glass-like [[mineral]]; an [[allotrope]] of [[carbon]] in which each atom is surrounded by four others in the form of a [[tetrahedron]]
#: ''He gave her '''diamond''' earrings.''

===Noun===
'''diamond''' (plural: [[diamonds]])<!-- pretty sure it can also be used as an uncountable noun as a material -->

#A glimmering shining glass-like [[mineral]]; an [[allotrope]] of [[carbon]] in which each atom is surrounded by four others in the form of a [[tetrahedron]]
#: The saw is coated with '''diamond'''.''
#A ring made of the material '''diamond'''.''
#: ''What a beautiful engagement '''diamond'''.''
#A person with a sparkling personality
#: ''She was a '''diamond'''.
#A color that is nearly white and a little blue.
#a square or equilateral parallelogram placed so that the longest axis is from top to bottom.
#{{baseball}} The field of play used for [[baseball]].
#: ''The teams met on the '''diamond'''.''
#A [[suit]] for [[playing card]]s
#: ''But I have the eight of '''diamonds''', Gin!.''

